# React: Slideshow App

## Description
Basic slideshow application built with React, where the user can navigate between slides using control buttons.

## Requirements
- *Node.js 18 LTS or higher*
- [Download & Install Node.JS](https://nodejs.org/)

## Installation
```bash
npm install
```

## How to Run
```bash
npm start
```

## How to Test
```bash
npm test
```

## Features
- Displays the first slide when the application starts
- *Next* button: advances to the next slide (disabled on the last slide)
- *Prev* button: goes back to the previous slide (disabled on the first slide)
- *Restart* button: returns to the first slide (disabled when already on the first slide)

## Component Structure
The `Slides` component receives an array of slides as a prop. Each slide is an object with the following properties:

| Property | Type   | Description       |
|----------|--------|--------------------|
| title    | string | Slide title        |
| text     | string | Slide content       |

## Test Attributes (data-testid)
| Element          | data-testid      |
|------------------|------------------|
| Restart button   | button-restart   |
| Prev button      | button-prev      |
| Next button      | button-next      |
| Slide title      | title            |
| Slide text       | text             |

## Main File
`src/components/Slides.js`
